[If you are not,]

123
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:16,880
you could go outside

124
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:19,480
and sleep with the stars all night.

125
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:40,040
Let's leave it at that for tonight.

126
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:41,320
Just make do.

127
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:42,680
But the necessary rules

128
00:10:42,680 --> 00:10:43,600
must still be followed.

129
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:44,720
No one is allowed

130
00:10:44,720 --> 00:10:45,840
[to cross this line.]

131
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:50,960
I can't sleep.

132
00:11:52,040 --> 00:11:52,920
I might as well go out and

133
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:54,400
share the night with the stars and moon.

134
00:12:36,640 --> 00:12:37,920
Why are you coming out?

135
00:12:38,680 --> 00:12:40,520
I've already given you the room.

136
00:12:47,280 --> 00:12:48,480
The candles in the room are out.

137
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:50,400
It's too dark for me to sleep.

138
00:12:57,120 --> 00:12:57,840
You should have someone

139
00:12:57,840 --> 00:12:59,080
light the candles.

140
00:13:00,040 --> 00:13:00,840
Shen Du,

141
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:02,080
it's the middle of the night,

142
00:13:02,080 --> 00:13:03,680
are you trying to disturb everyone?

143
00:13:03,880 --> 00:13:04,760
You weren't asleep either

144
00:13:04,760 --> 00:13:05,880
when the candles were lit, right?

145
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:07,040
Tossing and turning,

146
00:13:07,040 --> 00:13:08,240
it made it hard for me to sleep.

147
00:13:11,800 --> 00:13:12,880
Even the candles were lit,

148
00:13:12,880 --> 00:13:13,680
it's not bright enough.

149
00:13:19,160 --> 00:13:20,080
Still a bit dim.

150
00:13:23,560 --> 00:13:26,040
You're really quite strange.

151
00:13:26,440 --> 00:13:27,720
My father even specially

152
00:13:27,720 --> 00:13:28,920
lit a few more candles tonight.

153
00:13:28,920 --> 00:13:29,880
You still think it's dark?

154
00:13:30,040 --> 00:13:30,760
You're going to sleep,

155
00:13:30,760 --> 00:13:31,840
not studying or writing.

156
00:13:31,840 --> 00:13:33,560
Why does it have to be so brightly lit?

157
00:13:33,560 --> 00:13:34,960
It's not like you're blind and can't see.

158
00:13:40,160 --> 00:13:41,320
[Now I understand]

159
00:13:41,360 --> 00:13:43,040
[why Shen Du is called White Death.]

160
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:44,520
[Look at this place,]

161
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:46,920
[it's like a mourning hall during the day.]

162
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:48,200
[At night,]

163
00:13:48,440 --> 00:13:50,080
[it's still as bright as day.]

164
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:52,360
[Who brings a lantern]

165
00:13:52,360 --> 00:13:53,240
[to kick some ass?]

166
00:13:53,240 --> 00:13:54,280
[I can't do it without light.]

167
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:57,360
[Could it be that he's been]

168
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:36,240
[cursed with the moonless sight?]

169
00:14:49,280 --> 00:14:50,800
Tonight is truly rare.

170
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:52,320
Look, the

171
00:14:52,880 --> 00:14:55,800
Azure Dragon's Seven Stars in the east.

172
00:14:57,520 --> 00:14:58,320
And

173
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:01,280
the Vermilion Bird's Seven Stars in the south.

174
00:15:04,240 --> 00:15:05,280
You can see them all.

175
00:15:10,640 --> 00:15:11,440
Look over there.

176
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:14,000
Those four stars are connected.

177
00:15:14,040 --> 00:15:15,960
Do they like the four corners of a square?

178
00:15:19,160 --> 00:15:20,160
Those four over there

179
00:15:20,320 --> 00:15:21,560
are the Dituhe constellation.

180
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:23,040
There are four more below,

181
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:24,440
which are the Horned Serpent Stars.

182
00:15:25,560 --> 00:15:27,200
[Indeed, he can't really see.]

183
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:29,440
[There are no stars at all.]

184
00:15:33,040 --> 00:15:34,080
You know so much

185
00:15:34,080 --> 00:15:35,280
about the names of these stars.

186
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:36,880
You're quite impressive.

187
00:15:38,840 --> 00:15:39,840
What about that one over there?

188
00:15:39,880 --> 00:15:42,240
Looks like a rabbit.

189
00:15:42,240 --> 00:15:43,520
What's that one called?

190
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:52,280
That's called the Celestial Crow.

191
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:54,560
What about this one here?

192
00:15:54,560 --> 00:15:55,400
[I think it looks like]

193
00:15:55,400 --> 00:15:56,800
a flower cake.

194
00:15:57,160 --> 00:15:58,160
And the one in the south,

195
00:15:58,160 --> 00:15:59,160
[it looks like]

196
00:15:59,160 --> 00:16:00,640
the outline of a

197
00:16:00,640 --> 00:16:01,760
cherry.

198
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:03,200
It's called the Jingmu'an.

199
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:04,760
That doesn't sound nice.

200
00:16:04,760 --> 00:16:05,680
Let's change its name.

201
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:08,920
I think

202
00:16:09,480 --> 00:16:10,640
we should call it

203
00:16:11,280 --> 00:16:12,640
Cherry Stuffed Bread.

204
00:16:12,880 --> 00:16:14,360
Next to it is

205
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:15,360
the Flower Cake.

206
00:16:15,760 --> 00:16:16,800
It's better, how?

207
00:16:17,680 --> 00:16:19,040
Such strange names.

208
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:20,800
And they're all pastries.

209
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:22,800
You wouldn't understand,

210
00:16:22,800 --> 00:16:24,680
but naming them after food is better.

211
00:16:24,880 --> 00:16:26,880
When I was little, I had a poor appetite,

212
00:16:27,040 --> 00:16:28,800
so my mother gave the stars in the sky

213
00:16:28,800 --> 00:16:30,440
names of pastries.

214
00:16:30,760 --> 00:16:32,760
[She led me to believe that the]

215
00:16:32,760 --> 00:16:34,080
[stars' shine signaled more pastry eating.]

216
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:34,840
Otherwise,

217
00:16:34,840 --> 00:16:35,520
that star

218
00:16:35,520 --> 00:16:36,840
would never shine again.

219
00:16:39,320 --> 00:16:40,120
[Today,]

220
00:16:40,280 --> 00:16:42,280
[you need to eat more flower cakes.]

221
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:45,280
[Because today, the star that looks like]

222
00:16:45,280 --> 00:16:47,200
[a flower cake is shining.]

223
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:48,520
[My mother said,]

224
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:50,280
[if you don't eat it,]

225
00:16:51,120 --> 00:16:52,320
[that star]

226
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:53,480
[will go out.]

227
00:16:53,800 --> 00:16:54,720
[Help yourself.]

228
00:17:27,120 --> 00:17:28,439
What are you doing?

229
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:30,679
[Could she be]

230
00:17:31,840 --> 00:17:32,600
[you?]

231
00:18:54,080 --> 00:18:54,880
Sir.

232
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:17,760
What's the matter?

233
00:19:18,040 --> 00:19:19,200
Mr. Han went to see

234
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:20,360
Lord Yan earlier,

235
00:19:20,360 --> 00:19:21,760
saying that he's gonna say something.

236
00:19:21,880 --> 00:19:22,680
[He asked me]

237
00:19:22,680 --> 00:19:24,440
[to invite you both to join them.]

238
00:19:25,080 --> 00:19:25,680
Okay!

239
00:19:28,760 --> 00:19:29,960
We will be there.

240
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:48,800
[Lord Commander.]

241
00:19:48,800 --> 00:19:49,600
No formalities.

242
00:19:51,280 --> 00:19:52,000
Greetings,

243
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:52,760
Lord Commander.

244
00:19:53,920 --> 00:19:54,720
[Thank you for giving me]

245
00:19:54,840 --> 00:19:56,280
chance to be honest with myself.

246
00:19:56,960 --> 00:19:57,760
My love,

247
00:19:58,360 --> 00:19:59,680
what exactly do you want to say?

248
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:05,880
Caiwei,

249
00:20:07,440 --> 00:20:08,320
[I lied to you.]

250
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:12,160
My parents still have one son living.

251
00:20:12,400 --> 00:20:14,120
He's a confidant of Her Royal Highness and

252
00:20:14,640 --> 00:20:15,560
serves as the Deputy Minister of Rites,

253
00:20:16,920 --> 00:20:17,760
Zhang Baohuan.

254
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:23,200
Lord Zhang?

255
00:20:28,720 --> 00:20:29,960
But there's one thing I don't understand.

256
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:32,360
Since you are Lord Zhang's brother,

257
00:20:32,840 --> 00:20:33,560
then why doesn't he

258
00:20:33,560 --> 00:20:34,960
use his resources to protect you

259
00:20:35,120 --> 00:20:36,760
from the persecution of Princess Ying?

260
00:20:38,160 --> 00:20:38,960
Brother?

261
00:20:40,560 --> 00:20:41,760
Princess Ying, having discovered

262
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:43,400
[our relationship,]

263
00:20:44,080 --> 00:20:45,160
[wished to enlist me as her courtier,]

264
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:46,240
[motivated by a wish to]

265
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:48,480
challenge the Great Grandmother.

266
00:20:52,760 --> 00:20:53,960
I have repeatedly refused,

267
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:56,240
[but it's hard to escape.]

268
00:20:56,960 --> 00:20:58,480
[Although we are siblings,]

269
00:20:58,880 --> 00:21:00,440
he is unworthy of being my brother.

270
00:21:02,920 --> 00:21:04,280
He didn't save my sister.

271
00:21:05,680 --> 00:21:06,480
Sister?

272
00:21:12,120 --> 00:21:13,760
The owner of Jinxiu Workshop

273
00:21:14,760 --> 00:21:16,200
was your sister, Zhang Baoying?

274
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:21,800
Caiwei,

275
00:21:22,840 --> 00:21:23,640
I'm sorry.

276
00:21:25,160 --> 00:21:26,280
I lied to you.

277
00:21:28,520 --> 00:21:30,000
[Back when the incident happened,]

278
00:21:30,640 --> 00:21:32,040
[our whole family was exterminated.]

279
00:21:32,800 --> 00:21:34,520
[Zhang Baohuan used his connections]

280
00:21:34,520 --> 00:21:35,400
to save me.

281
00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:37,280
I have always wondered,

282
00:21:37,800 --> 00:21:39,080
he saved me already,

283
00:21:39,480 --> 00:21:41,040
how come he couldn't save my sister?

284
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:43,400
[I hate him for not being able to save her.]

285
00:21:44,320 --> 00:21:45,680
[I also hate myself for being powerless.]

286
00:21:47,320 --> 00:21:48,280
[At that time,]

287
00:21:48,800 --> 00:21:50,040
I made up my mind

288
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:54,000
to cut ties with the Zhang Family.

289
00:21:54,720 --> 00:21:55,880
My mother's surname is Han.

290
00:21:56,280 --> 00:21:57,400
I took her surname, and

